greeting: Greetings from The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences! http://oeis.org/

results.name: a(n) = index of n in A266117 or 0 if n is not present in that sequence.
comment: It is conjectured that A266117 is not just injective, but also surjective on N, i.e., that it is a true permutation of natural numbers. In that case also this sequence is a true permutation, and no hypothetical zero-values are ever needed.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..12634
Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
program: (Scheme, with code for A266117 defined with defineperm1-macro also required)
(define (A266118 n) (A266117 (- n))) ;; This returns inverse values of A266117 from its hidden cache.
xref: Inverse: A266117 (with provisions, see comment section).
